<i>December 15, 2013, there was
a brewing power struggle.</i>

06:09.133 --> 06:12.934
<i>between Salva Kiir Mayardit,
president of South Sudan...</i>

06:16.774 --> 06:20.108
<i>...and Riek Machar, the
former first vice president.</i>

06:23.881 --> 06:27.515
<i>And of course at the center
of power, is oil, is money.</i>

06:27.551 --> 06:30.952
<i>It became a conflict
along tribal lines:</i>

06:30.988 --> 06:33.254
<i>the Dinka, where the
president comes from,</i>

06:33.290 --> 06:37.725
<i>and the Nuer, where the former
first vice president comes from--</i>

06:37.760 --> 06:40.495
<i>and that engulfed
the whole country.</i>

06:40.530 --> 06:42.963
<i>With the country's
two largest tribes divided</i>

06:42.999 --> 06:45.866
<i>by their loyalty to the president
and the vice president,</i>

06:45.902 --> 06:50.071
<i>the world's newest country
